Jobres:
Key responsibilities include:-
•	Conduct emerging technology scans and experimentation with cross-functional business and technology teams to identify potential technology opportunities for strategic impact;
•	Engage and collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to raise the level of digital awareness and capabilities and to achieve alignment between business and IT strategies;
•	Lead and manage VITAL’s digital committee representatives from various functions to support business case development and to identify and pilot digital initiatives;
•	Plan and implement initiatives to drive adoption of digital and automation tools by VITAL officers to improve their work processes;
•	Curate and design content to share information on digitalisation and innovation best practices and trends with VITAL officers;
•	Maintain and enhance VITAL’s Digital and Robotic Process Automation Bot Library Portals on SharePoint; and
•	Identifying, analysing, and interpreting data using statistical techniques for management information/ reporting.

You will lead a team to review, formulate and implement strategies to – 

1.	Drive MOH’s value-driven care programme for continuous improvement in patient outcomes and cost efficiency;
2.	Promote cross-cluster/institutional collaborations or public-private partnerships in the creating value in healthcare;
3.	Develop national best practice standards in the delivery of care;
4.	Implementation of an appropriate Casemix classification and coding system as a source of data for policy development; and
5.	Work with MOH divisions and external organisations to advance MOH’s quality and patient safety agenda.

To develop an effective mental health ecosystem, you will support the Office to implement the National Mental Health and Well-being Strategy in, but not limited  to the following areas: 

General Population
a)	Review and develop care models, monitor implementation and progress, and manage funding of mental health programmes and services for the general population;
b)	Implement the initiatives under the National Dementia Strategy (NDS);
c)	Review the psychiatric intermediate and long-term care (ILTC) landscape and care models, and develop and monitor progress of the psychiatric ILTC services and facilities.

Youth
a)	Review and develop care models, monitor implementation and progress, and manage funding of youth mental health programmes;
b)	Develop and manage psychiatric ILTC and associated programmes and services for youths;
c)	Maintain policy oversight and coordinate mental health promotion and preventive pieces undertaken by relevant partner agencies

·	Analyse and understand the intersection of tech and industry developments, to identify salient trends and the opportunities/threats they present for Singapore; 
·	Formulate policy responses to advance Singapore’s longer-term interests, including by developing policy principles, and deploying the full suite of Government interventions within the economic domain (e.g. innovation and infrastructure investments, regulations, partnerships, direct provision, accreditation, and standard-setting, among others); 
·	Work across other parts of Government (including the agencies mentioned above) to translate growth in the Digital Economy into opportunities for value creation and good jobs, while managing trade-offs in the security and social domains;
·	Strategically review the budgets and programmes for Digital Economy initiatives delivered by our statutory boards

You might be interested in this job if you:

·	Are challenge-oriented and outcomes-driven, and thrive on dynamic team-based environments; 
·	Enjoy hunting for opportunities, and prefer creating new value in nascent areas
·	Have expertise and networks in economic and tech development, and enjoy working on long-term Government solutions for systemic and generational impact.

Jobreq:
·	Background in STEM, Law, Economics, Social Sciences preferred
·	Experience in public policy or project management roles within the tech industry would be advantageous; 
·	Strong analytical, evaluating and synthesizing skills, with the ability to communicate effectively in both written and spoken form; 
·	A learner’s mindset, with diverse interests (especially within the tech and media domains); 
·	Team players with strong leadership and inter-personal skills, including working with a wide range of industry and institutional stakeholders


We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates would be notified.

•	Possess tertiary qualification in any discipline and at least 5 years of relevant work experience;
•	Working knowledge of labour laws, industrial relations practices, or dispute resolution would be an advantage;
•	Experience in legal, regulatory, enforcement or policy work is preferred
•	Ability to write clearly and reason compellingly
•	Timely, analytical, independent and self-motivated
